Package com.github.westonpace.jayvee.workflow

Interface Summary
Sink<T> A data sink that items are pushed into.
Source<T> A source that data can be 'pop'ed from.
Worker An object that can be iterated to process data from sources into sinks.
 

Class Summary
DirectCallBuffer<T> A buffer which can be used for OnRequestOnly workers.
StandardWorker A standard worker implementation which provides logic for signalling when a worker has ended.
SystemBuilder A programmatic interface for building systems and subsystems.
WorkflowSystem Controller for a collection of workers.
WorklessWorkerRunnable  
 

Exception Summary
BufferEndedException An exception thrown when trying to access a buffer that someone has already called end on (and all other items have emptied out)
 

Annotation Types Summary
InputBuffer A marker used to indicate that a particular field or property is an input Source to a worker or system.
OnRequestOnly
